predicate.comments:
Holds if `expr` has a provably empty range. For example:

10 < expr and expr < 5

The range of an expression can only be empty if it can never be
executed. For example:

```cpp
if (10 < x) {
if (x < 5) {
// Unreachable code
return x; // x has an empty range: 10 < x && x < 5
}
}
```

